<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,697,1874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1669,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="321">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[324,574,1669,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,574,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="321">Drycothaea vulcanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[582,674,1669,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[582,674,1669,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="321" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Buquet, 1857" authorityName="Buquet" authorityYear="1857" box="[828,1172,1669,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridescens">
<emphasis box="[828,990,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="321">D. viridescens</emphasis>
(Buquet, 
<number box="[1105,1165,1669,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="321" value="1857.0">1857</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs as follows: antennomere III about 
<number box="[418,453,1706,1730]" pageId="1" pageNumber="321" value="1.4">1.4</number>
times longer than scape; punctures on pronotum not very distinct; scutellum almost entirely glabrous. In 
<taxonomicName box="[384,544,1741,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridescens">
<emphasis box="[384,544,1741,1765]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="321">D. viridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the antennomere III is slightly longer than scape (about 
<number box="[1176,1211,1742,1766]" pageId="1" pageNumber="321" value="1.1">1.1</number>
times), the pronotal punctures are distinct, and the scutellum is not glabrous.
</paragraph>
